            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="Job-026-fn1" type="footnote">JSul.I.04: The Karaim equivalent
                            of the standard Hebrew Job 26:1 is not included in the text, probably
                            intentionally, see Job 3:1, 4:1, etc. for similar cases. We reconstruct
                            this verse on the basis of ADub.III.84. The Hebrew text is not omitted,
                            see BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">וַיַּעַן
                                אִיֹּוב וַיֹּאמַר </foreign>
                            ‘And Job answered and said’ (Job 26:1). | C: <emph>Da ǯoɣap berdi Ijov
                                da ajtty</emph>. | QB: <emph>Da ǯoɣap berdi Ijov da ajtty</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>Da qaruv berdi Ijov da ajtty</emph>. | Kobeckaitė
                            (2019): <emph>Da qaruv berdi Ijov da ajtty</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-026-fn2" type="footnote">A North-Western Karaim form, cf.
                            SWKar. <emph>bolustunmo</emph> &amp;lt; MSWKar. <emph>boluštunmo</emph>
                            &amp;lt; MWKar. *<emph>boluštuŋmo </emph>&amp;gt; NWKar.
                                <emph>boluštujmo</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-026-fn3" type="footnote">A North-Western Karaim form, cf.
                            SWKar. <emph>qutqardynmo</emph> &amp;lt; MWKar. *<emph>qutqardyŋmo
                            </emph>&amp;gt; NWKar. <emph>qutqardynmo</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-026-fn4" type="footnote">Hypercorrect form of
                                <emph>bilegin</emph>.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
